text.tspan: As a matter of law, Federal criminal statutes prohibit unauthorized uses of the Seal. DHS policy prohibits granting authorization for certain commercial
uses of the Seal. It is permissible to reference DHS in materials if limited to true, factual statements. The words DHS and/or Homeland Security should
appear in the same color, font, and size as the rest of the text in any document. Such references should not imply in any way an endorsement of a product,
company, or technology. Use only the approved digital artwork les and never typeset, recreate or alter the seal or signature. Any change will cause inconsis
tencies, lessening the impact and compromising the trust of the Homeland Security seal and signature. For further questions, contact branding@dhs.gov.
